  "doc_id": "18611",
  "text": "We recently proposed a socio-cognitive computing paradigm [CITATION_1] that incorporates some socio-psychological mechanisms -in particular, mechanisms of taking the perspective of and inspiration from another agent -into classic ACO systems. We have conducted a number of experiments with the application of this socio-cognitive ACO approach for solving the TSP (Traveling Salesman Problem) and adapting PSO (Particle Swarm Optimization) algorithms in a similar way (thus, creating socio-cognitive PSO). PSO was applied to the problem of global optimization in the continuous domain [CITATION_2] .",
